Warm sunny day- some algal blooms- shoreline is covered with weeds.
Warm- sunny day- algal bloom.  Shoreline is covered with algae- makes getting out boat difficult.
Very windy- strong undertow.  Algae blooming golden and green- very thick on shore and shallow water.
Calm and sunny day- algal full bloom- turning brown.
Calm overcast day- algal bloom ending.
Partly sunny- lake is higher than normal due to excess rain.
Very windy- cloudy day- visible green seeds- strong under tow.
Sunny- calm day- algae turning brown.  Green seeds floating in water.
Partly sunny- soft wind- strong under tow- most algae growth has fallen to the bottom of the lake. Ice-on 12/12
Overcast skies- breezy- cool rainy weather so far this year. Algae very green and avg. 2 ft off lake shore.
Sunny day w/ soft breeze. We have had a lot of rain. Algae growth remains about 2 ft off lake shore
Sunny day- light winds. Algae has really multiplied. At least 10 ft off shore makes rowing out difficult
Overcast- slightly breezy day. Algae is about 30 ft off shore and is beginning to turn brown. Rowing is extremely difficult along shoreline
Sunny- breezy day. Algae is in bloom. Lake has a greenish brown substance floating on surface
Bright sunny day with soft winds. Most of the algae has sunk to the bottom of the lake
Bright sunny calm day. Green film floating along lake surface. Weeds have sunk making rowing much easier
Overcast- calm day- algae growth along shore (green substance afloat) .
Sunny- calm- algal bloom- many weeds make rowing difficult. Some small black/brown substance floating in water.
Light breeze- sunny- water is brown- algae has sunk- many particles suspended in water.
Sunny calm day-algal bloom. some type of bluish-gray substance clinging to algae and shoreline-no smell noticed   Lake level: very high
Sunny- calm day.  Lots of algae and weeds.  Hard to row off shore.
Sunny- calm.  Unusually cool.  Weeds down.
Had a wind storm 2 days ago.  Overcast.  Breezy.
